<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611925>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 19. Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, dextral pedipalp chela, dorsal (A, C) and retrolateral (B, D) aspects, illustrating carinae and distribution of trichobothria. A, B. Mesomexovis punctatus (Karsch, 1879), comb. nov., 8 (AMNH). C, D. Paravaejovis hoffmanni (Williams, 1970), 8 (AMNH). Scale bars 5 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4611925/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611953>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 28. Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, metasomal segments I–V and telson, lateral aspect, illustrating carinae. A. Balsateres cisnerosi (Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom, 2004), comb. nov., 8 (IBUNAM). B. Konetontli acapulco (Armas and Martín-Frías, 2004), comb. nov., holotype 8 (IBUNAM). C. Paravaejovis pumilis (Williams, 1980), 8 (AMNH). Scale bars 5 2.5 mm (A), 1 mm (B, C)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4611953/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611869>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 1. Representative species in the North American vaejovid scorpion subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905. A. Chihuahuanus bilineatus (Pocock, 1898), comb. nov., ♀; B. Kochius bruneus (Williams, 1970), 8; C. Mesomexovis punctatus (Karsch, 1879), comb. nov., 8; D. Syntropis macrura Kraepelin, 1900, ♀; E. Thorellius sp., 8; F. Vizcaino viscainensis (Williams, 1970), comb. nov., 8. Photos in B, D and E courtesy of R. Mercurio." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4611869/files/figure.png" .

